Narcos: Cartel Wars


Narcos: Cartel Wars is a strategy game where you manage a drug empire and fight the leaders of other cartels. To guide you through the first steps of the game, you have help from none other than Pablo Escobar (from the series, of course).


The game system in Narcos: Cartel Wars is very similar to Clash of Clans and other games like it. The most important thing is to create an operations base that provides you with all the resources needed to maintain your empire while taking defensive measures to fight off enemy attacks. It's also very important to hire sicarios so you can attack your enemies.


Narcos: Cartel Wars has more than a dozen types of buildings to construct. You can also add stories to these buildings to get more resources from them, though to do so you'll first need to level up. And there's no better way to level up than by attacking your enemies.


Narcos: Cartel Wars is a simple strategy game with good graphics but a pretty unoriginal premise. But in any case, it's still an excellent use of the Narcos license.


